				\begin{document}$$L{A}_{h}={e}^{-k.\sum _{i=1}^{{N}_{h}}LA{I}_{i}}$$\end{document}LAh=e−k.∑i=1NhLAIiwhere LAh is the light availability at height h in the canopy, k is a coefficient of attenuation (with k = 0.25), LAIi is the leaf area index of the tree i, and Nh is the number of trees with a height superior to h.

